works.description: The star highlight of Bonhams’ Space History Sale, Alexei Leonov’s flown space suit, has sold for a whopping $242,000, exceeding its presale estimate of between $100,000 and $150,000. Alexei Leonov, the commander of the Soyuz 19 spacecraft, wore this space suit during the historic 1975 Apollo Soyuz Test Project. It was the first time that the Americans and the Soviets met in space with their spaceships.
